claims:
Claims 1. Sanitary product (100) comprising a back sheet (102), having an outer surface (130) and an inner surface (120), a core (104) and a front sheet (106) joined with a joining periphery (108) in a sandwich structure with the core (104) fully comprised within the joining periphery (108) and arranged between the back sheet (102) and the front sheet (106) with the inner surface (120) of the back sheet (102) facing the core (104), and configured with a long direction (110), a perpendicular short direction (112) and a product periphery (114) characterized in that the back sheet (102) is configured with: - a printed circuit (122) on the inner surface (120), which printed circuit (122) com- prises a connector (124) configured with a connector width (126) and a sensor (128) for humidity detection, preferably fluid detection; - a stiffener (132) for increasing the bending force of the back sheet (102) arranged on the outer surface (130) opposite the connector (124) configured with a stiffener width (136) extending beyond the connector width (124); and - two through-going incisions (140) in the long direction (110) between which inci- sions (140) the connector width (126) is comprised, the incision going through at least the stiffener (132) and the back sheet (102), and with one end of each incision (140) ending at the product periphery (114) or at an intersecting cut (144), such that a flap (150) is comprised in the back sheet (102) comprising the connector (124) and part of the stiffener (132), wherein the joining periphery (108) encircles a smaller area than the product periphery (114) and is comprised within the product periphery (114) and where the connector (124) and the two through-going incisions (140) in the long direction (110) are out side the joining periphery (108). 2. Sanitary product (100) according to claim 1 wherein the stiffener (132) is config ured with a stiffener width (136) in the short direction (112) in the range of 20-35 mm, preferably in the range 25-30mm and a stiffener length (138) in the long direction (110) in the range of 5 -20mm, preferably in the range 10-15 mm. 3. Sanitary product (100) according to any one of the preceding claims wherein the flap (150) comprised in the back sheet (102) comprising the connector (124) and part of the stiffener (132) is adapted for inserting into and connecting to a transmitter unit (10). 4. Back sheet supply (200) comprising multiple back sheets (102) comprised in the sanitary product (100) according to claim 1, said back sheets (102) having an outer surface (130) and an inner surface (120), characterized in that the back sheets (102) are pre-fabricated with a printed circuit (122) on the inner surface (120) comprising a connector (124) with a connector width (126) and a sensor (128) for humidity detec- tion, preferably fluid detection. 5. Fabrication plant (300) for sanitary products (100) with a production direction (302) adapted for receiving a feed of back sheets (102) comprised in a back sheet supply (200) according to claim 4 and for receiving a feed of cores (104) and front sheets (106) from a core supply (210A) and a front sheet supply (210B), which fabrication plant is characterized in, that it comprises: - a stiffener applicator (310) configured for applying a stiffener element (312) to the back sheets (102) for increasing the bending force of the back sheet (102) on the outer surface (130) opposite the connector (124) configured with a stiffener width (136) extending beyond the connector width (124); - an incision device (320) configured for applying through-going incisions (140) in the production direction (302) on either side of the connector (124), the incision going through the stiffener element (312) and the back sheet (102); - a joining device (330) configured to join a back sheet (102) with a core (104) and a front sheet (106) with a joining periphery (108) and with the core (104) fully com prised within the joining periphery (108); and - a product cutting device (340) for applying a final product cut (342) comprising one or more through-going cuts (344), defining a product periphery (114) of the sanitary product (100), wherein - the stiffener applicator (310) and the incision device (320) are arranged before the joining device (330); - the back sheet (102) and the core (104) and the front sheet (106) are arranged with the inner surface (120) facing the core (104) in the joining device (330); - the joining device (330) is configured to join the back sheet (102) with the core (104) and the front sheet (106) such that the connector (124) is outside the joining periphery (108); and 

 - the product cutting device (340) is configured to apply a through-going cut (342) intersecting the through-going incisions (140) in the production direction (302) such that a flap (150) is created in the back sheet (102) comprising the connector (124) and part of the stiffener element (314). 6. Fabrication plant (300) according to claim 5 wherein the incision device (320) comprises rotating drums comprising active cutting means (322) for applying through- going incisions (140) in the production direction (302) and pressure means (324) for pressing the back sheet (102) with applied stiffener element (312) against the active cutting means (322) which means (322,324) are displaced relative to each other when the back sheet (102) with applied stiffener element (312) is displaced in between the means (322,324) in the production direction (302). 7. Fabrication plant (300) according to claim 5 wherein the incision device (320) comprises a laser (326). 8. Fabrication plant (300) according to any one of the preceding claims 5 to 7 config ured to run with a production speed (360) of up to 400m/min. 9. Method (400) for producing a sanitary product (100) comprising acts of: - Providing (410) a back sheet (102) configured with an inner surface (120) and an outer surface (130), wherein the back sheets (102) are pre-fabricated with a printed circuit (122) on the inner surface (120), comprising a connector (124) configured with a connector width (126) and a sensor (128) for humidity detection, preferably fluid detection; - Applying (420) a stiffener element (312) to the back sheet (102) for increasing the bending force of the back sheet (102) on the outer surface (130) opposite the connect or (124) configured with a stiffener width (136) extending beyond the connector width (124); - performing (430) two through-going incisions (140) in the production direction (302) on either side of the connector (124) going through at least the stiffener element (312) and the back sheet (102); - Providing (410) a core (104) and a front sheet (106); 

 - joining (440) the back sheet (102) and the core (104) and the front sheet (106) with the inner surface (120) of the back sheet (102) facing the core (104) to provide a join ing periphery (108) with the core (104) fully comprised within the joining periphery (108); and - performing (430) a final product cut (342) comprising one or more through-going cuts (304) defining a product periphery (114) of the sanitary product (100), wherein the connector (124) is comprised outside the joining periphery (108) and an intersecting cut (144) which intersects the through-going incisions (140) in the pro duction direction (302), such that a flap (150) is created in the back sheet (102) com- prising the connector (124) and part of the stiffener element (312). 10. Method (400) according to claim 9 wherein the back sheets (102) are provided as a continuous web comprising a further act of exerting a general tension to the interme diate products in the production direction (302), such that the back sheets (102) are extended in length in the long direction (110). 11. A sanitary product (100) according to any one of the preceding claims 1 to 3 ob tained by the method (400) for producing a sanitary product (100) according to any one of the preceding claims 9 or 10.
